                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d301">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">868.51 War Credits/579: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Greece (<persName type="from">Morris</persName>)
                        to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Athens</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-11-17T13:00:00+02:00"
                            >November 17, 1932—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received November 17—9:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>132. Your 63, November 13, 3 p.m. British Government today notified International
                    Financial Commission to include American Government debt in request to the Greek
                    Government for transfer of 30 percent interest payment. French and Italian
                    agreement to this expected by tomorrow. A meeting of the Greek political party
                    leaders this evening will decide whether to pay 30 percent, according to London
                    agreement and whether to include therein the American debt.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Morris</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
